<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99792635064683></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99792635064683><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6026&mid=99792635064683>nice weapon, and i don't mind farmers</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6026&mid=99792635064683#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85584><span id=Scholar>barfly</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>83 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 15th 9:45 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some nice chanter gave me (lvl 7 dwarf warrior) this along with the BA longsword while I was brewing in FP, just minding my own business -- said she had a difficult time giving it away (she was asking around for newbies at the gate, but her friends were telling everyone not to trust her...)<br><br>Read alot of complaints about the higher levels farming this type of loot from Runnyeye, and this is a perfect example of why this activity benefits lower levels such as myself.&nbsp;&nbsp;People will pick up whatever looks nice and drag it back to the Freeport mall thinking they can get a good price.  Problem is, everyone there is looking for lammys, fungi and whatnot that simply prices out anything lower -- can't even read the auctions they fly by so fast.  So any middle range items get lost in the crowd.  Furthermore, why bother with something that is only going to provide a small amount of money for these folks when thousands of plat are being traded by the minute.  Look who's hanging out in north FP (on M. Marr server) and you see 70% lvl 50 and above, with a few newbies fighting the lag to drop-off their bat wings at the bank.<br><br>Being one of the few non-twinks in FP also helps (I couldn't even give away my fine steel weapons after receiving these).  Long live the farmers (the generous ones, at least).<br><br>Great weapon -- easily worth a few hundred plat -- but you can obtain it for much, much less if you are patient and respectful (and in the right place at the right time).<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
