	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 16th 9:20 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just got one of these in the re-vamped Runnyeye, and I want to try to explain something here.&nbsp;&nbsp;I notice a lot of people saying Mithril 2hs is better, and I would agree, Mithril is better because of the haste....and that is it.  The haste makes a Mithril 2HS something like dmg 21 dly 31 to 35 or so.  So, lets say it dmg 21 dly 31 for grins, which is the best I have seen proposed and do a quick calc dmg/dly = 0.677 ( I know this isn't the excepted method, but it still works for comparisons)  The Black Alloy Bastard Sword = 24/39 =0.615  Bigger number = better.<br><br>But let us continue the comparison.  Many say there are a lot better 2hs weapon out there, and there may be, if you have 1000's and 10,000's of plat avalible.  For me, a 40 ranger (highest character so non-twinked who is now practicing 2hs to use this), I have seen what passes for weapons before and after.  Just looking at the Dmg/dly and comparing weapons, there are a TON of weapons lower dmg/dly than a BABS that drop off level 45+ MOBS.  Over half the off of the alter planes.<br><br>The BABS is incredible for the level it takes to get it.  A good group of mid to low level 30's (or maybe even high 20's) could go into Runnyeye and claim one of these.  Jade reavers and other weapons all take a guild raid to get (almost) of 45+ level characters.<br><br>So<br> 1. BABS drops off a lower level MOB, though rare.<br> 2. Beats out a lot of harder to get weapons<br> 3. Has +3 Poison sv (not a big deal)<br> 4. Weight = 2.5 stones<br> 5. Greater Light Source (somewhat usefull)<br><br>  That last one is the most important one I think.  It might as well be weightless, and can be swung all day by an almost encumbered warrior.<br><br>1K plat, is in my opinion, to low a price for one of these.  I think more like 5K plat is like it.  What it comes down too is "what would I pay to kill monsters faster and not loose stamina?"<br><br>So - take it as you will, but for a player moving through the ranks without twinking benifits, this is an awsome 2hs<br><br>-Zar<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
